{
  "stem": "2723.2",
  "chunk_idx": 13,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I think I had a very, very rude awakening when she, a day later, found her way to me only to tell me, 'Who are you?' And when I identified myself and told her of the link, [INAUDIBLE] said 'So bloody what?' and walked away.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that was my growing-up period.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I worked in the kitchen in Auschwitz, which was hard work, but I was always interested in-- in cooking, and I knew how to handle preparation, and I could peel vegetables.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I didn't have to go through the beating that some did who couldn't peel fast enough, who didn't know how to cut vegetables, and assured the Germans that they had maids to do it, only to be beaten black and blue on admission of that fact.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't know the time, but I do know that it was already very bitterly cold.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because as part of our kitchen duty, I had to have frequent washings, German style.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I presume the food was-- preparation was for them, because otherwise, why would they have bothered?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember the terror of that Friday-- because it was always on Friday.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I did mention to you before that I had a skin condition at that stage.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were being checked every Friday by Dr.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Mengele for our health, which meant having the shower, the dreaded shower, then parading in front of him.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he had eyes that saw every little blemish.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I befriended someone who was very dear to me, who confided that she was two months pregnant.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Nothing could be seen, but he did see it, and she was taken from me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "That was the last person, more or less, that I had left, who belonged to my sanity.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
